      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KISAUNI (1) ran below his best last time finishing seventh (31.15) over 530m at Angle Park in a OPEN. Solid winning record at this trip. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Key runner on his best form. PAW LOUIS (2) was spotting a start early but made a sustained run to place when third (17.50) at Murray Bridge Straight in Invitation. Has failed to finish in the placings from two starts here. Has performed well from this box with a win and nine minor placings to his name from 15 starts. Expected to be in the finish again. HI THERE FRANK (7) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 1.75 lengths at Angle Park in a handy 19.88 beating Attention Seeker. Can make it two on the bounce. ALL THE SASS (8) is always hard to beat when he races here at this trip.",
